==========================================================================
4. RHOAI DATA SCIENCE PROJECT
==========================================================================

Dashboard URL:     {{ rhoai_dashboard_url }}
Project name:      {{ partner_namespace }}

Log in with your OpenShift credentials (section 1). Your Data Science
Project is named "{{ partner_namespace }}" and contains:

{% if enable_rhoai_workbenches %}
  Workbenches (one per user, CPU-only):
{% for user in workbench_users %}
    - {{ user.workbench_name }} (owned by {{ user.username }})
{% endfor %}
{% if enable_rhoai_shared_gaudi_workbench %}
    - shared-gaudi (shared, requests 1 Gaudi card)

  IMPORTANT: shared-gaudi is shared across all users in your namespace.
  Start it when you need an HPU card for training, STOP IT when you're
  done. Habana cards aren't time-sliced — leaving shared-gaudi running
  monopolizes the card. There are 8 cards on the cluster and they're
  shared across all partners.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if enable_rhoai_dspa %}
  Data Science Pipelines: enabled (DSPA v2)
  Connect from a workbench using the pre-injected pipeline endpoint.
{% endif %}

  Data Connection: "MinIO ({{ partner_namespace }} bucket)"
{% if rhoai_create_partner_bucket %}
  Your dedicated bucket: {{ partner_namespace }}
{% else %}
  Shared bucket: ai-demo
{% endif %}

  Attach this connection to a workbench from the dashboard, and the
  AWS_* environment variables will be injected at workbench start.

{% endif %}
==========================================================================
5. SUPPORT
==========================================================================

Channel Manager: {{ partner_channel_manager | default('your Arrow contact') }}

For technical issues with the lab environment, open a ticket via your
channel manager. Lab access expires {{ partner_expiration_date }}.

==========================================================================
6. KNOWN LIMITATIONS
==========================================================================

  - Operator install modes: Only OwnNamespace / SingleNamespace operators
    can be installed by partners. AllNamespaces operators (RHOAI, OpenShift
    Pipelines, MTV, GitOps, etc.) are pre-installed cluster-wide.

  - RHOAI workbench start/stop on this cluster version may fail with a
    webhook error if the underlying RHOAI version has the
    extractElyraRuntimeConfigInfo bug. If you hit this, contact your
    channel manager — there is a workaround that requires cluster-admin.

  - EDA does not have organizational scoping in this AAP version.

